    'Heat oil in a large pot. Add beef and cook until browned on all sides. Remove beef and set aside. In the same pot, add onions and garlic. Cook until onions are translucent. Stir in tomato paste, then pour in Guinness. Add back the beef. Add carrots, potatoes, beef broth, bay leaves, salt, and pepper. Cover and simmer for 2 hours or until the beef is tender. Garnish with fresh parsley before serving.',
    '- 1 lb (450g) stewing beef, cubed\n- 2 tablespoons vegetable oil\n- 2 onions, chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 2 tablespoons tomato paste\n- 1 can (14 oz) Guinness beer\n- 3 carrots, peeled and sliced\n- 2 potatoes, peeled and cubed\n- 2 cups beef broth\n- 2 bay leaves\n- Salt and pepper, to taste\n- Chopped fresh parsley, for garnish',
    'Beef',
    '2023-10-23',
    'https://www.recipetineats.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Irish-Beef-Guinness-Stew_6.jpg?resize=650,910'
);
INSERT INTO Recipes (Name, Description, Ingredients, Category, SubmissionDate, ImageUrl)
VALUES (
    'Beef and Vegetable Soup',
    'In a large pot, brown beef over medium-high heat. Remove and set aside. In the same pot, sauté onions and garlic until translucent. Add carrots, potatoes, beef broth, diced tomatoes, dried thyme, salt, and pepper. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 1.5 to 2 hours or until beef is tender. Garnish with fresh parsley before serving.',
    '- 1 lb (450g) beef stew meat, cubed\n- 1 onion, chopped\n- 2 cloves garlic, minced\n- 3 carrots, peeled and sliced\n- 2 potatoes, peeled and cubed\n- 4 cups beef broth\n- 1 can (14 oz) diced tomatoes\n- 1 teaspoon dried thyme\n- Salt and pepper, to taste\n- Chopped fresh parsley, for garnish',
    'Beef',
    '2023-10-24',
